_exists

IPredicate _exists(IItemQueryModel aQueryModel,
                   IField lhs,
                   IField rhs,
                   IPredicate aPredicate)
Creates a correlated subquery with the root query model target class joined with the target class of the input arg aQueryModel, using an equi join on the two input args lhs and rhs. Finally a filter predicate maybe supplied in aPredicate. 

 // The following example queries the database to find contributors with 
 // no mentor. Let us assume mentor relationship information is defined
 // using "mentor" link type 
   
 ContributorQueryModel contribQueryModel = contribQueryModel.ROOT;
 AuditableLinkQueryModel linksQueryModel = AuditableLinkQueryModel.ROOT;
   
 // get mentor link type
 String mentorLinkType = "mentor" + UUID.generate();
 IPredicate mentorPredicate = linksQueryModel.name()._eq(mentorLinkType);
   
 // construct predicate
 IPredicate findContributorsWithMentorsPredicate = contribQueryModel._exists(
         linksQueryModel, contribQueryModel.itemId(), 
         linksQueryModel.sourceRef().referencedItem().itemId(),
         mentorPredicate);
 IPredicate findContribWithNoMentorsPredicate = findContributorsWithMentorsPredicate._not();

 // construct a Contrib query with the predicate
 IItemQuery query = IItemQuery.FACTORY.newInstance(contribQueryModel);
 query.filter(findContribWithNoMentorsPredicate);

 queryService.queryItems(query, IQueryService.EMPTY_PARAMETERS, 10);

Parameters:
aQueryModel - is an instance of a query model
lhs - is the left hand side of the equijoin condition
rhs - is the right hand side of the equijoin condition
aPredicate - is a filter condition for the correlated subquery
Returns:
an instance of a Predicate

0.7
